Figure 4 visualises the relationship between LUM and normalised traffic flow across zone types and modes. All three modes show positive associations with land use mix, consistent with theoretical expectations. Regression slopes differ substantially: the active mode slope is steepest (, ), reflecting pedestrian-scale sensitivity to functional diversity, while motor vehicle flows show the shallowest slope (, ).
