Figure 6 reports SHAP importances and residual spatial autocorrelation diagnostics. Land use mix is the leading predictor for motor vehicle () and active modes (), while transit stop density ranks first for public transit (). Employment accessibility shows relatively uniform importance across modes, consistent with its role as a trip attractor independent of mode choice.
